[eval] expr.error1.a: conflicting values 4 and 3:
    ./in.cue:6:5
    ./in.cue:7:5
[eval] expr.error2.a: conflicting values 4 and 3:
    ./in.cue:11:5
    ./in.cue:12:5
[structural cycle] listConcat.error1.a: error in call to list.Concat: structural cycle:
    ./in.cue:17:5
[structural cycle] listConcat.error2.a: error in call to list.Concat: structural cycle:
    ./in.cue:22:5
-- out/todo.txt --
listConcat.error1/error2.a: v2 shows list elements inside structural cycle error, v3 shows proper error message.
selfEmbed.ok2.a and ok6.a: v2 expands a as independent struct, v3 uses structure sharing ~(x).
issue4125: not present in v2 (feature added later), only evaluated in v3.
